Topic Author's Original Post - Mar 29, 2007 - 11:22am PT

She's the greatest, although she couldn't make it in show business today since she wasn't an anorexic self-absorbed bimbo.

"I never knew how good our songs were until I heard Ella Fitzgerald sing them," --Ira Gershwin.

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Rb6LG6ENkM Wild Bill

Gary, thanks for that. I am really into old live recordings. I wish we could figure out how to make music play as soon as the thread is opened.

Here's a studio recording of Ella and Louis Armstrong doing 'Summertime.' So sweet, reminds me of a branch swaying in the breeze

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1yKgAEkCKxY&mode=related&search=

The town that Nature forgot to hate

Mar 29, 2007 - 12:21pm PT

First time I paid (my own) money to see a performance, June '67,

it included Ella Fitzgerald, with a pretty good backup band,

led by a guy called Duke Ellington. Gal could sing, eh?

Word on My Funny Valentine, though.

Sarah Vaughn put on some absolute tour de force renditions with

piano accompaniment. Owned the damn thing. Brought tears to my

eyes. Standing Strong

wherever you are ella - thank you! Wild Bill
